From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] hw/misc/applesmc: replace zero sensor defaults
 with realistic iMac20,1 values

The existing applesmc device exposes only six keys (REV, OSK0,
OSK1, NATJ, MSSP, MSSD). macOS's AppleSMC client polls a few
dozen temperature/voltage/fan sensors at boot and on a 1 Hz
timer thereafter; every key that is not in the device returns
NOEXIST (or, with patch 1 of this series, a zero payload
logged at LOG_UNIMP). On a zero payload the client code treats
the sensor as "broken" and retry-polls at an elevated rate,
generating log spam and unnecessary I/O on every boot.

Populate the key set with realistic idle values for an
iMac20,1-class x86 host. SP78 is the 16-bit big-endian fixed
point used for temperature (top 8 bits integer degrees C,
bottom 8 bits fraction). fpe2 is used for fan RPM (raw = RPM
<< 2). Values are read from a live iMac20,1 at idle; they
bracket the real hardware envelope but are otherwise static --
a future patch may drive them from QEMU-visible host metrics.

The sensor groups covered are:
  * CPU: TC0F, TC0P, TCXc
  * GPU: TG0F, TG1F, TGDD, TG0P
  * Storage: TH0P, TH1A, TH1C, TH1F
  * Display: TL0V, TL1V
  * Memory: TM0P, TM0V
  * Power / ambient: Tp00, Tp2F, Ts0S, TS0V, Ts1S, Ts2S, TB0T,
                     TB1T, TB2T, TA0V, TVMD, TVmS, TVSL, TVSR
  * Platform power rails: PC0R, PCPC, PCPG, PCPT, PfCP, PfCT,
                          PfGT, PfHT, PfM0, PfST, PSTR, PHDC
  * Fan: FNum, F0Ac, F0Mn, F0Mx

This brings the live error rate on macOS 15 guests from
~9000 SMC errors per 5 s down to single digits.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
---
 hw/misc/applesmc.c | 73 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 73 insertions(+)

--- a/hw/misc/applesmc.c
+++ b/hw/misc/applesmc.c
@@ -495,7 +495,73 @@
     applesmc_add_key(s, "NATJ", 1, "\0");
     applesmc_add_key(s, "MSSP", 1, "\0");
     applesmc_add_key(s, "MSSD", 1, "\0x3");
+
+    /*
+     * GPU temperature sensors. SP78 format: 16-bit big-endian with the
+     * top 8 bits encoding integer degrees C and the bottom 8 bits the
+     * fraction. Returning zeroed sensors caused macOS to flag these as
+     * broken and retry-poll. Values approximate a warm idle iMac20,1.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TGDD", 2, "\x46\x00");  /* GPU diode: 70 C */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TG0P", 2, "\x41\x00");  /* GPU proximity: 65 C */
+
+    /*
+     * Fan control (iMac20,1 has one chassis fan). fpe2 format: raw
+     * value is RPM << 2, big-endian. Idle ~1500 RPM, range 1200-3600.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "FNum", 1, "\x01");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "F0Ac", 2, "\x17\x70");  /* current: 1500 RPM */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "F0Mn", 2, "\x12\xC0");  /* min:     1200 RPM */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "F0Mx", 2, "\x38\x40");  /* max:     3600 RPM */
+
+    /*
+     * Temperature sensors covering the rails the macOS AppleSMC client
+     * polls on an iMac20,1-class host. Values are realistic idle
+     * readings in SP78 (big-endian) format; zeros trigger retry storms
+     * on broken-sensor paths.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TC0F", 2, "\x48\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TC0P", 2, "\x41\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TCXc", 2, "\x55\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TG0F", 2, "\x41\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TG1F", 2, "\x41\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TH0P", 2, "\x2E\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TH1A", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TH1C", 2, "\x2E\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TH1F", 2, "\x2E\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TL0V", 2, "\x25\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TL1V", 2, "\x27\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TM0P", 2, "\x2D\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TM0V", 2, "\x2D\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "Tp00", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "Tp2F", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "Ts0S", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TS0V", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "Ts1S", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "Ts2S", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TB0T", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TB1T", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TB2T", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TA0V", 2, "\x1A\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TVMD", 2, "\x32\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TVmS", 2, "\x32\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TVSL", 2, "\x32\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "TVSR", 2, "\x32\x00");
 
+    /* Power and platform rails (12 keys). */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PC0R", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PCPC", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PCPG", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PCPT", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfCP", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfCT", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfGT", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfHT", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfM0", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PfST", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PSTR", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "PHDC", 2, "\x00\x00");
+
     /*
      * #KEY - Apple SMC convention for "total key count". macOS reads
      * this at boot and iterates 0..count-1 via
